[From November 2019 to January 2020, 19 outbreaks due to FMD type SAT 2 were reported in cattle in the municipalities of Molemole, Polokwane, Greater Letaba, Makhado and Ba-Phalaborwa in Limpopo Province.

Total animals affected
Species / Susceptible / Cases / Deaths / Killed and disposed of / Slaughtered
Cattle / 18891 / 138 / 0 / 6 / 8619

This event still continuing, with the last follow-up sent to the OIE on 25 Sep 2020 https://www.oie.int/wahis_2/public/wahid.php/Reviewreport/Review?page_refer=MapEventSummary&reportid=34771. The event summary and map can be seen at https://www.oie.int/wahis_2/public/wahid.php/Reviewreport/Review/viewsummary?reportid=32311

Since March 2020, 12 outbreaks due to FMD type SAT 2 have been reported in cattle in the municipality of Bushbuckridge, Mpumalanga Province.

Total animals affected
Species / Susceptible / Cases / Deaths / Killed and disposed of / Slaughtered
Cattle / 8888 / 74 / 0 / 0 / 0

The event still continuing, event summary and map are available at https://www.oie.int/wahis_2/public/wahid.php/Reviewreport/Review/viewsummary?reportid=33576. - Mod.CRD

